Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship with Omninuera for the position of AI Intern. This letter outlines the principal terms of the internship and the steps required to accept and onboard. This draft is intended for HR and Legal review; placeholders are included where further detail or policy citations are required.

1. Position and Reporting
- Role: AI Intern
- Duration: 3 months (three months), commencing on [Start Date] or such other date as may be mutually agreed.
- Work mode: Completely remote.
- Jurisdiction / Location for applicable policies: Bengaluru, India.
- Reporting to: [Supervisor Name] (or their designate).

2. Expected Commitment
- Working hours / expected commitment: Standard internship expectation is part-time approximately 20 hours per week. The intern and Omninuera may agree in writing to increased hours or a full-time arrangement during the internship period. Working schedule is flexible and to be agreed with your supervisor. All working hours should comply with applicable labour laws and company policy [Company Policy Reference].

3. Stipend
- Amount: INR 10,000 (Indian Rupees Ten Thousand) per month.
- Payment schedule: Stipend will be paid monthly, subject to submission of any required attendance/onboarding forms, and will be credited to the intern's nominated bank account on or before the 7th calendar day of the following month, unless otherwise agreed. Any applicable taxes or statutory deductions will be handled in accordance with law and company policy [Company Policy Reference].
- The stipend is intended as a training stipend and does not constitute a salary or employment wages. This internship does not in itself create an employment relationship unless a separate employment agreement is executed.

4. Location and Jurisdiction
- Although the role is remote, for the purposes of jurisdiction, applicable employment and internship regulations, and dispute resolution, the intern's place of work shall be deemed Bengaluru, India, unless otherwise specified in a further agreement.

5. Confidentiality and Non-Disclosure
- Confidentiality: During and after the internship, you must keep confidential all proprietary information, trade secrets, business plans, technical information, algorithms, models, datasets, and other confidential information of Omninuera and its clients that you access or develop. This obligation continues beyond the internship period.
- NDA: You will be required to sign Omninuera's standard Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA) as part of onboarding. See attached/linked policy [Company NDA Reference]. Legal should review the NDA for adequacy and any required modifications.

6. Intellectual Property and Work Product Ownership
- IP assignment: All inventions, developments, works of authorship, discoveries, designs, code, models, datasets, documentation, and other materials created, developed, or conceived by you during the internship, either alone or jointly with others, that relate to Omninuera's business or are created using company resources (collectively, Work Product), shall be the sole and exclusive property of Omninuera. You agree to assign and hereby assign all right, title, and interest in such Work Product to Omninuera.
- Moral rights: Where applicable, you agree to waive or assign any moral rights or similar rights to the extent permissible by law.
- Further steps: You will be required to sign an IP assignment and related agreements upon or before the start of the internship. Legal review required for jurisdictional compliance.

7. Onboarding Requirements
To commence the internship, the following must be completed and submitted:
- Signed copy of this offer letter or electronic acceptance (see Next Steps / Acceptance below).
- Signed NDA and IP assignment agreement.
- Bank account details for stipend deposit (bank name, branch, account number, IFSC).
- Proof of identity and address (e.g., Aadhaar, PAN, Passport, Driver's License) as per company policy and applicable law.
- Completed onboarding forms (tax declaration, background verification consent, emergency contact information).
- Any other documents requested by HR or Legal (e.g., academic enrollment or proof of student status if applicable).

8. Background Checks and Eligibility
- This offer is conditional upon satisfactory completion of background verification, identity, and eligibility checks as required by Omninuera and permitted by law.
- If you are required to hold specific enrollment status (e.g., student), you may be required to provide proof of such status.

9. Termination and Notice
- Either party may terminate the internship relationship by providing two weeks' written notice to the other party. The Company may terminate the internship immediately for cause, which includes but is not limited to breach of confidentiality, material misconduct, misrepresentation, gross negligence, violation of law, or failure to comply with company policies.
- On termination, you agree to return all company property and confidential information in your possession, including but not limited to electronic files, devices, and documentation.
- Stipend on termination: Payment for the last incomplete month will be pro-rated to the date of termination and processed in the next scheduled stipend payment, subject to deductions for any amounts owed to the company and compliance with applicable law.

10. Compliance with Laws and Company Policy
- The internship will be governed by applicable Indian labour laws and any applicable internship regulations. This offer and the internship are subject to compliance with applicable policies such as [Company Internship Policy Reference], [Employment Policy Reference], and other internal policies. Legal review required to confirm statutory compliance.
- Omninuera reserves the right to amend policies from time to time; where changes affect you, HR will advise you in writing.

11. Workplace Conduct and Company Policies
- You are expected to adhere to company policies on code of conduct, data privacy, information security, acceptable use, and any other policies applicable to interns. Relevant policies include: [Company Code of Conduct Reference], [Data Protection Policy Reference], [Information Security Policy Reference].

12. Expenses and Equipment
- Company equipment and access: Any company-owned hardware, software, or access credentials provided to you remain company property. Use must be in accordance with company policy.
- Expenses: Unless expressly authorized in writing, Omninuera will not reimburse expenses incurred by you while performing the internship duties. Any approved reimbursable expenses must follow prior written approval and submission of receipts per company policy [Expense Policy Reference].

13. No Guarantee of Employment
- Completion of the internship does not guarantee an offer of employment. Any subsequent employment offer would be subject to separate terms and approvals.

14. Miscellaneous
- Entire agreement: This offer letter, together with the NDA and IP assignment and any referenced policies, constitutes the full understanding between you and Omninuera with respect to the internship.
- Amendments: Any amendments must be in writing and signed by an authorized representative of Omninuera.
- Governing law and dispute resolution: To be determined in consultation with Legal. Suggested governing law: laws of India with venue in Bengaluru for disputes, subject to Legal review.

